Sunday Aborisade The Senate said on Friday that it had put machinery in motion towards collaborating with the executive arm of government by coming up with achievable National Development Plans. The red chamber said the plan would serve as basis upon which yearly budgets were planned and executed. The Chairman, Senate Committee on National Planning and Economic Affairs, Senator Olubunmi Adetunmbi, stated this at a news conference in Abuja. To achieve this, he said the Senate and the Federal Ministry of Finance, Budget and National Planning, would jointly hold a retreat on Monday. He said the forum would deliberate on the yearly budgeting and implementation. He added that the retreat was designed among to develop and build consensus, explore opportunities for technical support, capacity building, and share best practices targeted at facilitating a return to plan-based budgeting in Nigeria.” He explained that though the N10.59tn 2020 budget recently passed by both chambers of the National Assembly would kick start the return of the yearly budget cycle to January – December, the 2021 budget would be more collaborative in vision, content and execution. CopyrightPUNCH.
